article.headline: Sam Houston St. 107, Auburn 89
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. -- Gilberto Clavell scored 34 points, going 14-of-17 from the field, to lead Sam Houston State to an 107-89 victory against Auburn on Sunday for the school's first victory against a Southeastern Conference opponent. Corey Almond added 25 points and Lance Pevehouse had 13 off the bench for Sam Houston State (7-3), which shot 57.6 percent from the field. Auburn's Frankie Sullivan tied the game at 28 with two foul shots, but the Bearkats pulled away with 8:41 left in the half. Sam Houston State shot 65.6 percent from the field and 9 of 15 from the 3-point line to take a 58-42 halftime lead. Auburn (5-6) pulled within 86-72 with 8 minutes left in the game, but Sam Houston State hung on. It was the most points Auburn has allowed since 1994, when Arkansas defeated the Tigers 117-105. DeWayne Reed led Auburn with 19 points and Tay Waller scored 18.
